<div style="border-left:5px solid #E6EED6; border-right:5px solid #E6EED6; padding:10px 20px; background:#160C13; font-family:Geo; letter-spacing:1px; font-size:16px; margin:2em;">
{{Collapse|num=1|initial=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Description</span>|final=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Are you proud of yourself?</span>|body=}}
----
{{Blurimage|file=Minus100Inside.png|caption=What is that thing?}}
<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">The exterior banging of the spacecraft never seems to stop or lessen as one travels through '''Level 140'''. The cramped spacecraft makes it difficult for those at or above <span title="6 feet 6 inches">2 meters</span>, as much of it has been constructed with a low roof. Alongside additional pipes and fixtures, those above <span title="6 feet">1.8 meters</span> my regularly risk hitting their head against the features. While taller segments exist, the level is mainly built around these spaceship corridors.</span> 

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">According to the most recent explorations done, '''Level 140''' no longer has a day and night cycle. This old cycle had a 16 hour day period, with two 1.5 hour segments for sunset and sunrise, and a 5 hour night period. This cycle was one built into the spaceship, with loud bell noises playing after the sunrise period and before the sunset period. This noise could be heard across the entire level. Though currently, the display system responsible for showing the time has been broken. The display board, appearing in the "commonplace" rooms of '''Level 140''', now only display a bright red color, with some variance of cyan and green closer to the cracks. This has lead the bell noises to grow distorted and play inconsistently until death.</span>

{{Blurimage|file=Minus100Medical.png|caption=How familiar, and how unknown.|align=left}}
<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Outside of the commonplace and corridors, wanderers can traverse through medical wards, offices, and storage facilities.</span>

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">The medical wards appear very high tech upon entry, with fluorescent white fixtures being the only natural source of light in '''Level 140'''. However, many of these remain in various condition, and continue to grow defunct as routine cleaning appears to be nonexistent. While the medical wards often have great access to supplies, they also are commonly host to the entities in the level, with the most condensed population of entities in the level appearing there.</span>

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Some medical wards have their own hazardous properties as well, with rouge equipment being seen attacking and killing wanderers through rapid surgical operations. These surgeries vary, showing no consistent pattern among them. If neither of these hostile forms appear, the medical wards can function as [[Phenomenon 18|Safe Places]]. Medical wards may include [[Object 6|Moth Jelly]], [[Object 34|Spice of Life]], [[Object 19|Portable Purifiers]], and other general medical supplies. Groups of Wanderers often bunk here, with various levels of hostility towards others.</span></div>


<div style="border-left:5px solid #E6EED6; border-right:5px solid #E6EED6; padding:10px 20px; background:#160C13; font-family:Geo; letter-spacing:1px; font-size:15px; margin:2em;">
{{Collapse|num=2|initial=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Continuation</span>|final=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Is this what you wanted?</span>|body=}}
----
{{Blurimage|file=Minus100storage.png|caption=When will the lights stop flashing?|align=right}}
<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">The rarest segment of '''Level 140''' are the offices. These spaces are the smallest, only having an average area of 3 meters. Many offices feature bedding, desks, and personal cabinets. Some offices may have access to windows, which often are 3d displays of other levels in the Backrooms. Because of their rarity, it's unknown if these segments may host entities within them, though some have reported seeing [[Entity 88|Amalgamations]] in the offices.</span>

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Signified by flashing red lights and muted sirens, storage rooms are the largest rooms in '''Level 140'''. They take form of standard corridors, with additional branching hallways to reach other sectors. These sectors often contain a variety of unnecessary supplies, mostly items found in [[The Frontrooms]]. These items are held in large boxes spanning across multi-story shelves. Estimations of quantity reach in the tens of thousands, with many hailing it to be an endless supply.</span>

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">However, attempts to move items out of storage have commonly lead to death, as '''Level 140''' boasts a complex security system. Wanderers who are caught trying to leave storage rooms with items were blocked off through laser grid walls. Compressed of high energy beams of heat, touching them will cause immediate disintegration to the object. The only way to leave storage when this occurs is to remove any items originally found in the segment. Laser grids have been tested to immediately activate when a wanderer grabs an item or an item is within <span title="2 feet">0.6 meters</span> from the exit. All exits to other levels found in storage will also feature the laser grids.</span></div>


<div style="border-left:5px solid #E6EED6; border-right:5px solid #E6EED6; padding:10px 20px; background:#160C13; font-family:Geo; letter-spacing:1px; font-size:15px; margin:2em;">
{{Collapse|num=3|initial=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Entities</span>|final=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Have you no sense of decency?</span>|body=}}
----
{{Blurimage|file=Minus100Office.png|caption=It's quiet here...|align=left}}
<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Much of the entities in '''Level 140''' are ones commonly found across the backrooms, with some variation. All entities found still behave in the same way they do in other levels, their only difference often being a shift in appearance.</span>

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Entities such as [[Entity 5|Clumps]] and [[Stalkers]] display some sort of decay when found in '''Level 140'''. This decay takes form of extreme degloving, displaying mass amounts of bloodshed which would likely be fatal to any other instance of these entities. However, testing has shown them to have a higher than average heartbeat, leading to more blood production, and therefore supplying enough blood to be able to continue functioning like its other counterparts.</span>

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Some sections of the storage facility host the only known physical appearance of [[Perfect Emptiness|<span style="color:red">[FILE MISSING]</span>]], leading to much further speculation on the nature of '''Level 140''' and the entities that live inside of it. These versions of the entity appear to be emaciated humanoids which appear perfectly blended into the environment around them. <span style="color:red">[FILE MISSING]</span> blend into the level around them, only being noticeable by a striped appearance that continually moves upward on their body. These stripes appear slightly brighter or darker than the surrounding area. Wanderers who have claimed to interact with <span style="color:red">[FILE MISSING]</span> described being unable to process its existence at all, only able to see a black fuzz where it is. Because of the elusive nature and rarity of encounters, there are no recordings of successful attacks by the entity.</span>

<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Entities with greater roots in mental damage, such as [[Phenomenon 35|Wretches]], and [[Entity 71|Ballerinas]] appear with much more "physicality". To be specific, these entities seem unable to use their mentally hazardous properties and may only rely on their physical abilities to chase down wanderers. Why these skills are disabled is unknown.</span></div>


<div style="border-left:5px solid #E6EED6; border-right:5px solid #E6EED6; padding:10px 20px; background:#160C13; font-family:Geo; letter-spacing:1px; font-size:15px; margin:2em;">
{{Collapse|num=4|initial=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Entrances and Exits</span>|final=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Do you feel any remorse?</span>|body=}}
----
{{Blurimage|file=Minus100Screen.png|caption=Who did this? Why?}}
<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:20px;">Entrances</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Touching a toy spacecraft found sitting on a pedestal in [[Level 139]] will automatically transport one here.</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">If a gazebo is found in [[Level 498]], stepping inside of it may cause a glitch-like effect, where the level will melt into '''Level 140'''. This is recorded to be a 30% chance</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Finding "blood crystals" in [[Level 221]] or [[Level 8]] will send wanders to '''Level 140''' if they are broken. This is done via noclipping.</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Ordering "Mouthwash" in [[Level 128]] and drinking it will have wanderers appear in medical wards within '''Level 140'''. In a majority of cases, these sections are safe.</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Removed brass tiles in the ceiling or floor of [[Level 143]] open up to '''Level 140'''. However these are both noticeably rare and do not show the level until the wanderer has already gone through it.</span>

<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:20px;">Exits</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Any interactions with <span style="color:red">[FILE MISSING]</span> that lead in death will bring wanderers to [[Level 203]]. This is still a matter of theory, however, as no deaths by the entity have been reported.</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Breaking through the windows in the office will cause the wanders to spawn into the level shown.</span>
*<span style="text-shadow:0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40, 0em 0em 1.0em #BBC5AA40">Finding the boarding room and noclipping through the door will send wanderers to [[Level 24]]. Other space-like levels, such as [[P0LARI5]] have also been entered through this method.</span></div>


<div style="border-left:5px solid #E6EED6; border-right:5px solid #E6EED6; padding:10px 20px; background:#160C13; font-family:Geo; letter-spacing:1px; font-size:15px; margin:2em;">
{{Collapse|num=5|initial=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Open Addendum</span>|final=<span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC; letter-spacing:2px; font-size:25px;">>> Close Addendum</span>
