<div style="border:4px solid #DDDBCB; background:#050505; color:#F5F1F3; margin:1em; padding:10px; font-family:Geo; font-size:15px;">
<center><span style="font-family:Bruno Ace SC;"> Expedition Log 140-F </span></center> {{Underline|DDDBCB}}
<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Beginning log.. everyone shut up. ''[Chatter in the background dies down.]'' This is log F, the sixth expidition log through Level 140. The date is February 25th, 2018 and I am here with Amos, Fleet, and Huxley. We were sent in on behalf of the [[Backrooms Investigation Foundation||<span style="color:white;">BIF</span>]] regarding some new developments in the level. Was told there is some sort of "entity leakage" in the level, whatever that may entail.<br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''A. Amos:'''</span> Finally you said the full thing. ('''E.Hope:''' Fuck off.) Anyway where were we supposed to go? If it told us anything at all.<br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Were supposed to first find one of the common rooms, apparently some anomalies are happening there. <br>

''[Beyond this point, video recording is provided.]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''D. Huxley:'''</span> Ok, the camera is working too, does anything want to say anything to the camera before we get going?<br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''J. Fleet:'''</span> ''[Fleet takes the camera from Huxley, holding it to his face.]'' ...God i look disheveled. Looks like my hair was done by [[Slashers|<span style="color:white;">Captain Cutter</span>]]. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''A. Amos:'''</span> Nah, she would've done better than that bird's nest. ''[Background laughter from Hope]'' Can we get moving too? They didn't pay to stand around. <br>

''[The group moves through Level 140, details have been omitted for brevity]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> You got your camera set up? <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''D. Huxley:'''</span> Yea, yea. Looking for a money shot? <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Anyway, update to the log, we found one of the common rooms in Level 140. Apparently they look different.<br>

''[Huxley shows a photo to the camera, and older photo of the common place in Level 140]''
<br><br>
[[File:Previous102.png|center|400px]]
<br><br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> ''[Hope opens the door, stepping inside with her weapon drawn. Fleet follows behind her.]'' ...wow yea this is fucking different.<br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''J. Fleet:'''</span> Looks like someone put an axe through the monitor, what the hell. ''[Amos and Huxley enter]''<br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''A. Amos:'''</span> Holy shit.<br> 

''[Amos moves over to the wall, running his hand over it. The camera stays there until they hear the sound of humming]''<br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> We have a [[Entity 71|<span style="color:white;">Ballerinas</span>]] on sight, but it doesn't seem to... how do I put it? ('''J.Fleet:''' Like, entrance?) Yea, it's not entrancing at all. Is that usual for the level?<br>

''[Camera pans over to the Ballerina, no others in shot]''<br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''J. Fleet:'''</span> Yea I think so. None of the mental effects seem to do anything here. That's what the file said. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Ah, right. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''D. Huxley:'''</span> What else could be affected by the broken monitor? Outside or whatever day cycle was originally there. <br>

<span title="Amos has requested the BIF to keep this part in">''[Details have been omitted for brevity]'' </span><br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''A. Amos:'''</span> How many lions do you think you could beat in a fight? <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''J. Fleet:'''</span> Lions are terrifying, I'd lose no doubt. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Yea, I couldn't fight one either. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''A. Amos:'''</span> And you, Huxley? <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''D. Huxley:'''</span> 7. <br> 

''[Amos laughs, and walks over to Huxley. They high-five each other.]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''A. Amos:'''</span> My man. <br>

''[Skip foward to the group making their way to one of the offices]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Update to the log, we have made our way to one of the offices. Earlier we had to take out some [[Entity 5|<span style="color:white;">Clumps</span>]] and [[SPhenomenon 35|<span style="color:white;">Wretches</span>]], but beyond that nothing worth noting. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''D. Huxley:'''</span> Yea, there was, one of the medical rooms we found have 5 survivors in it. It was like 20 minutes ago and all I remember is that one of the members were named Jimmy. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''J. Fleet:'''</span> God that's such a shitty name. Only rancid vibes from someone who's named that. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Fine fine, we found a couple of survivors in one medical room and in another there was a corpse. You all happy with that? <br>

''[The camera moves up and down, as to nod in response]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''E. Hope:'''</span> Alright, anyway, we found an office. So were gonna check it out. Well, Amos is. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''A. Amos:'''</span> ''[Amos was already moving towards the door at this time, he looked to Hope indignantly]'' Damn, ok. <br>

''[All of them shuffle into the office, with Huxley taking up the rear. There is a pause for about 10 minutes]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''J. Fleet:'''</span> ...I think the only new change is that the "window" is changing more frequently. I think it's supposed to change every minute. It seems to be going every second. <br>
<span style="font-size:17px">'''D. Huxley:'''</span> Let me see, I got the camera. <br>

''[The others move out of the way, and Huxley points the camera to the window. Their assumption was correct. Though after about 30 seconds, the camera suddenly falls to the floor, and the video ends there]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px">'''D. Huxley:'''</span> Huh?! <br>

''[Audio transmission was cut soon after, as Fleet, Amos, and Hope went after the 4th member. According to them, Huxley was killed by a group of [[Entity 6|<span style="color:white;">Dullers</span>]]. His body would be found on later expeditions, with his wounds bearing a perfect match to the attack style of Dullers. All other members have returned alive.]'' <br>

<span style="font-size:17px"> [END LOG] </span><br>

